15 WHEREAS, his contributions to Jenkins County were recognized when he was named the
16 2014 Jenkins County Citizen of the Year, a testament to his commitment to community
17 service and civic engagement; and
18 WHEREAS, in addition to his professional and civic contributions, he is co-owner of
19 Brinson's Barbeque, an iconic family restaurant in Jenkins County founded by his parents in
20 1966, which he continues to operate alongside his two sisters; and
21 WHEREAS, Matt Brinson is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable
22 reputation for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
23 WHEREAS, he has served with honor and distinction with Planters EMC, and his vision and
24 unyielding commitment to advancing rural electric services will be sorely missed upon his
25 retirement; and
26 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
27 remarkable and distinguished individual be appropriately recognized.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body recognize and commend Matt Brinson for his many exemplary
30 years of service to Southeast Georgia; congratulate him upon the grand occasion of his
31 retirement; and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Matt
34 Brinson.
